5 STATE OF MAINE
6 HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 929, L.D. 1407, “An Act to Direct the
10 Board of Occupational Safety and Health to Develop Indoor Air Quality Standards for
11 Buildings in the State in Which Public Sector Workers Work”
12 Amend the bill by striking out the title and substituting the following:
13 'Resolve, Directing the Department of Labor to Report the Findings of the Indoor Air
14 Quality Advisory Group'
15 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the title and inserting the following:
16 'Sec. 1. Indoor air quality advisory group report. Resolved: That, on or before
17 December 3, 2025, the Department of Labor shall submit to the Joint Standing Committee
18 on Labor a report containing the findings of the indoor air quality advisory group, which
19 was convened in 2024 by the Department of Labor, Bureau of Labor Standards to advise
20 the Department of Labor, Board of Occupational Safety and Health on indoor air quality
21 matters that are beyond the standards set by the United States Department of Labor,
22 Occupational Safety and Health Administration. After reviewing the report, the committee
23 may report out legislation relating to the report to the Second Regular Session of the 132nd
24 Legislature.'
25 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
26 number to read consecutively.
27 SUMMARY
2288 This amendment, which replaces the bill with a resolve, is the majority report of the
2299 committee. The amendment directs the Department of Labor to report to the Joint Standing
3300 Committee on Labor on the findings and recommendations of the indoor air quality
3311 advisory group, which was convened in 2024 by the Department of Labor, Bureau of Labor
3322 Standards to advise the Department of Labor, Board of Occupational Safety and Health.
3333 FISCAL NOTE REQUIRED
3344 (See attached)
